    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-03-08T09:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-03-08T09:00:00-05:00" n="631"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d631">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/8884: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-03-08T16:00:00+02:00"
                            >March 8, 1941—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 6:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>888. The Embassy hears from a fairly reliable source that Gesandter Schwörbel,
                    Chief of the Southwestern [<hi rend="italic">Southeastern</hi>] European Section
                    of the German Foreign Office,<note n="42a" xml:id="d631fn42a">Paul Schwörbel,
                        head of the Division for Southeast Europe and the Near East in the News
                        Service and Press Department of the German Foreign Office.</note> is either
                    en route to or has arrived at Athens for the purpose of promoting a Greek
                    compromise settlement with Italy.</p>
                <p>Repeated to Athens.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
